<a name="arab105"><p><b>ARAB 105 Intensive Elementary Arabic (15)</b><br/>Develops the four communicative language skills: listening, speaking, reading, and writing. Stresses communication skills and emphasizes the links between language and culture, using mainly Modern Standard Arabic, with exposure to Egyptian Colloquial Arabic. Cannot be taken for credit if ARAB 101-ARAB 103, ARAB 411-ARAB 413 taken for credit. If Arabic is the student's language of admission only 10 credits count towards graduation<br/><a href="https://myplan.washington.edu/course/#/courses/ARAB105" target="_blank">View course details in MyPlan: ARAB 105</a></p></a>
<a name="arab199"><p><b>ARAB 199 Study Abroad (1-15, max. 15)</b><br/>Credit for elementary or intermediate Arabic in an approved Study Abroad program. Requires credit evaluation by department or faculty. Does not automatically apply to major or minor requirements. Offered: AWSpS.<br/><a href="https://myplan.washington.edu/course/#/courses/ARAB199" target="_blank">View course details in MyPlan: ARAB 199</a></p></a>
